Favorite Movies List â€“ PHP & MySQL Assignment

This project is a dynamic web application built using **PHP**, **MySQL**, and **HTML/CSS**. It displays a styled list of favorite movies stored in a MySQL database and dynamically rendered using PHP loops and logic. 

Fulfills all requirements of "Assignment 1 - PHP and MySQL".

Features

- Connects to a MySQL database using PHP
- Displays data dynamically using loops
- Conditional styling using PHP if/else logic
- Responsive and styled layout using HTML & CSS
- W3C-validated HTML5 and CSS3


Setup Instructions

> Prerequisites:
- [XAMPP](https://www.apachefriends.org/) (or any LAMP stack)
- PHP 7+
- MySQL
- Web browser
- Git (optional, for pulling repo)

---

### Start Apache and MySQL
- Open **XAMPP Control Panel**
- Click **Start** for both **Apache** and **MySQL**

---

### Import the Database

1. Open [http://localhost/phpmyadmin](http://localhost/phpmyadmin)
2. Create a new database named:



3. Run the following SQL to create the table and insert data:

```sql
CREATE TABLE movies (
id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
title VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
genre VARCHAR(50),
rating FLOAT,
release_date DATE,
poster_url TEXT
);

INSERT INTO movies (title, genre, rating, release_date, poster_url) VALUES
('Inception', 'Sci-Fi', 9.0, '2010-07-16', 'inception.jpg'),
('Interstellar', 'Adventure', 8.6, '2014-11-07', 'interstellar.jpg'),
('Titanic', 'Romance', 7.8, '1997-12-19', 'titanic.jpg'),
('The Matrix', 'Action', 8.7, '1999-03-31', 'matrix.jpg'),
('Avatar', 'Fantasy', 7.9, '2009-12-18', 'avatar.jpg');




